results.name: Number of primitive sublattices of index n in generic 3-dimensional lattice.
comment: These sublattices are in 1-1 correspondence with matrices
with acf = n, b = 0..c-1, d = 0..f-1, e = 0..f-1, gcd(a,b,c,d,e,f) = 1.
a(n) is the number of 2-generated subgroups of Z^3 with order n.
The Dirichlet convolution of a(n) with A010057 gives A001001.
Dirichlet convolution of A254981 and A000290.
link: Álvar Ibeas, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
Index entries for sequences related to sublattices
formula: Dirichlet g.f.: zeta(s) * zeta(s-1) * zeta(s-2) / zeta(3s).
Sum_{k=1..n} a(k) ~ Pi^2 * Zeta(3) * n^3 / (18*Zeta(9)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Feb 01 2019
xref: Cf. A001001, with which it agrees unless n is divisible by a cube.
